    "However, when the sparsity is non-uniformly applied in the LoHi, Decreasing, and Increasing schedules, the workload is no longer balanced, and the correlation breaks down.",
    "In the Speck, the sparsity schedule is programmed as spiking neuron thresholds per network layer, as exact sparsity cannot be induced.",
    "The LoHi and Increasing schedule curves have better performance at the same total sparsity, suggesting that the last network layer (which has the most weights) is the workload bottleneck.In effect, we confirm that total network measurements like activation sparsity can be correlated with performance benefits, but they are insufficient for fully understanding performance due to the parallelization of the network across neurocores.",
